verses.text_plain: Then the Lord answered Job out of the whirlwind, and said,
verses.verse_html: 1Then the Lord answered Job out of the whirlwind, and said,

verses.text_plain: Who is this that darkeneth counsel by words without knowledge?
verses.verse_html: 2Who is this that darkeneth counsel by words without knowledge?

verses.text_plain: Gird up now thy loins like a man; for I will demand of thee, and answer thou me.
verses.verse_html:
3Gird up now thy loins like a man; for I will demand of thee, and answer thou me. ▼
▼ answer…: Heb. make me know

footnotes.body_html: ▼ answer…: Heb. make me know

verses.text_plain: Where wast thou when I laid the foundations of the earth? declare, if thou hast understanding.
verses.verse_html:
4Where wast thou when I laid the foundations of the earth? declare, if thou hast understanding. ▼
▼ hast…: Heb. knowest understanding

tokens.text: wast thou when I laid the foundations

footnotes.body_html: ▼ hast…: Heb. knowest understanding

verses.text_plain: Who hath laid the measures thereof, if thou knowest? or who hath stretched the line upon it?
verses.verse_html: 5Who hath laid the measures thereof, if thou knowest? or who hath stretched the line upon it?

verses.text_plain: Whereupon are the foundations thereof fastened? or who laid the corner stone thereof;
verses.verse_html:
6Whereupon are the foundations thereof fastened? or who laid the corner stone thereof; ▼
▼ foundations: Heb. sockets
 , ▼
▼ fastened: Heb. made to sink?

footnotes.body_html: ▼ fastened: Heb. made to sink?

verses.text_plain: When the morning stars sang together, and all the sons of God shouted for joy?
verses.verse_html: 7When the morning stars sang together, and all the sons of God shouted for joy?

verses.text_plain: Or who shut up the sea with doors, when it brake forth, as if it had issued out of the womb?
verses.verse_html: 8Or who shut up the sea with doors, when it brake forth, as if it had issued out of the womb?

verses.text_plain: When I made the cloud the garment thereof, and thick darkness a swaddlingband for it,
verses.verse_html: 9When I made the cloud the garment thereof, and thick darkness a swaddlingband for it,

verses.text_plain: And brake up for it my decreed place, and set bars and doors,
verses.verse_html:
10And brake up for it my decreed place, and set bars and doors, ▼
▼ brake…: or, established my decree upon it

footnotes.body_text: ▼ brake…: or, established my decree upon it
footnotes.body_html: ▼ brake…: or, established my decree upon it

verses.text_plain: And said, Hitherto shalt thou come, but no further: and here shall thy proud waves be stayed?
verses.verse_html:
11And said, Hitherto shalt thou come, but no further: and here shall thy proud waves be stayed? ▼
▼ thy…: Heb. the pride of thy waves

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thy…: Heb. the pride of thy waves
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thy…: Heb. the pride of thy waves

verses.text_plain: Hast thou commanded the morning since thy days; and caused the dayspring to know his place;
verses.verse_html: 12Hast thou commanded the morning since thy days; and caused the dayspring to know his place;

verses.text_plain: That it might take hold of the ends of the earth, that the wicked might be shaken out of it?
verses.verse_html:
13That it might take hold of the ends of the earth, that the wicked might be shaken out of it? ▼
▼ ends: Heb. wings

verses.text_plain: It is turned as clay to the seal; and they stand as a garment.
verses.verse_html: 14It is turned as clay to the seal; and they stand as a garment.

verses.text_plain: And from the wicked their light is withholden, and the high arm shall be broken.
verses.verse_html: 15And from the wicked their light is withholden, and the high arm shall be broken.

verses.text_plain: Hast thou entered into the springs of the sea? or hast thou walked in the search of the depth?
verses.verse_html: 16Hast thou entered into the springs of the sea? or hast thou walked in the search of the depth?

verses.text_plain: Have the gates of death been opened unto thee? or hast thou seen the doors of the shadow of death?
verses.verse_html: 17Have the gates of death been opened unto thee? or hast thou seen the doors of the shadow of death?

tokens.text: unto thee? or hast thou seen

verses.text_plain: Hast thou perceived the breadth of the earth? declare if thou knowest it all.
verses.verse_html: 18Hast thou perceived the breadth of the earth? declare if thou knowest it all.

verses.text_plain: Where is the way where light dwelleth? and as for darkness, where is the place thereof,
verses.verse_html: 19Where is the way where light dwelleth? and as for darkness, where is the place thereof,

verses.text_plain: That thou shouldest take it to the bound thereof, and that thou shouldest know the paths to the house thereof?
verses.verse_html:
20That thou shouldest take it to the bound thereof, and that thou shouldest know the paths to the house thereof? ▼
▼ to the bound: or, at, etc

tokens.text: thereof, and that thou shouldest know

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to the bound: or, at, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to the bound: or, at, etc

verses.text_plain: Knowest thou it, because thou wast then born? or because the number of thy days is great?
verses.verse_html: 21Knowest thou it, because thou wast then born? or because the number of thy days is great?

verses.text_plain: Hast thou entered into the treasures of the snow? or hast thou seen the treasures of the hail,
verses.verse_html: 22Hast thou entered into the treasures of the snow? or hast thou seen the treasures of the hail,

verses.text_plain: Which I have reserved against the time of trouble, against the day of battle and war?
verses.verse_html: 23Which I have reserved against the time of trouble, against the day of battle and war?

verses.text_plain: By what way is the light parted, which scattereth the east wind upon the earth?
verses.verse_html: 24By what way is the light parted, which scattereth the east wind upon the earth?

verses.text_plain: Who hath divided a watercourse for the overflowing of waters, or a way for the lightning of thunder;
verses.verse_html: 25Who hath divided a watercourse for the overflowing of waters, or a way for the lightning of thunder;

verses.text_plain: To cause it to rain on the earth, where no man is; on the wilderness, wherein there is no man;
verses.verse_html: 26To cause it to rain on the earth, where no man is; on the wilderness, wherein there is no man;

verses.text_plain: To satisfy the desolate and waste ground; and to cause the bud of the tender herb to spring forth?
verses.verse_html: 27To satisfy the desolate and waste ground; and to cause the bud of the tender herb to spring forth?

verses.text_plain: Hath the rain a father? or who hath begotten the drops of dew?
verses.verse_html: 28Hath the rain a father? or who hath begotten the drops of dew?

verses.text_plain: Out of whose womb came the ice? and the hoary frost of heaven, who hath gendered it?
verses.verse_html: 29Out of whose womb came the ice? and the hoary frost of heaven, who hath gendered it?

verses.text_plain: The waters are hid as with a stone, and the face of the deep is frozen.
verses.verse_html:
30The waters are hid as with a stone, and the face of the deep is frozen. ▼
▼ is…: Heb. is taken

footnotes.body_html: ▼ is…: Heb. is taken

verses.text_plain: Canst thou bind the sweet influences of Pleiades, or loose the bands of Orion?
verses.verse_html:
31Canst thou bind the sweet influences of Pleiades, or loose the bands of Orion? ▼
▼ Pleiades: or, the seven stars: Heb. Cimah
 , ▼
▼ Orion: Heb. Cesil?

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Pleiades: or, the seven stars: Heb. Cimah
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Pleiades: or, the seven stars: Heb. Cimah

verses.text_plain: Canst thou bring forth Mazzaroth in his season? or canst thou guide Arcturus with his sons?
verses.verse_html:
32Canst thou bring forth Mazzaroth in his season? or canst thou guide Arcturus with his sons? ▼
▼ Mazzaroth: or, the twelve signs
 , ▼
▼ guide: Heb. guide them

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Mazzaroth: or, the twelve signs
▼ guide: Heb. guide them

verses.text_plain: Knowest thou the ordinances of heaven? canst thou set the dominion thereof in the earth?
verses.verse_html: 33Knowest thou the ordinances of heaven? canst thou set the dominion thereof in the earth?

verses.text_plain: Canst thou lift up thy voice to the clouds, that abundance of waters may cover thee?
verses.verse_html: 34Canst thou lift up thy voice to the clouds, that abundance of waters may cover thee?

verses.text_plain: Canst thou send lightnings, that they may go, and say unto thee, Here we are?
verses.verse_html:
35Canst thou send lightnings, that they may go, and say unto thee, Here we are? ▼
▼ Here…: Heb. Behold us?

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Here…: Heb. Behold us?

verses.text_plain: Who hath put wisdom in the inward parts? or who hath given understanding to the heart?
verses.verse_html: 36Who hath put wisdom in the inward parts? or who hath given understanding to the heart?

verses.text_plain: Who can number the clouds in wisdom? or who can stay the bottles of heaven,
verses.verse_html:
37Who can number the clouds in wisdom? or who can stay the bottles of heaven, ▼
▼ stay: Heb. cause to lie down

footnotes.body_text: ▼ stay: Heb. cause to lie down
footnotes.body_html: ▼ stay: Heb. cause to lie down

verses.text_plain: When the dust groweth into hardness, and the clods cleave fast together?
verses.verse_html:
38When the dust groweth into hardness, and the clods cleave fast together? ▼
▼ groweth…: or, is turned into mire: Heb. is poured

footnotes.body_text: ▼ groweth…: or, is turned into mire: Heb. is poured
footnotes.body_html: ▼ groweth…: or, is turned into mire: Heb. is poured

verses.text_plain: Wilt thou hunt the prey for the lion? or fill the appetite of the young lions,
verses.verse_html:
39Wilt thou hunt the prey for the lion? or fill the appetite of the young lions, ▼
▼ the appetite: Heb. the life

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the appetite: Heb. the life

verses.text_plain: When they couch in their dens, and abide in the covert to lie in wait?
verses.verse_html: 40When they couch in their dens, and abide in the covert to lie in wait?

verses.text_plain: Who provideth for the raven his food? when his young ones cry unto God, they wander for lack of meat.
verses.verse_html: 41Who provideth for the raven his food? when his young ones cry unto God, they wander for lack of meat.
